015/04/03/opinion/denmarks-drug-free-pigs.html" data-link><div class="kicker">Op-Ed Contributor</div><img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2015/04/03/opinion/03Estabrook/03Estabrook-thumbLarge.jpg" class="highlighted-thumb" width="150" height="150"/><span class="title">Denmark’s <span class="nobr">Drug-Free</span> Pigs</span><p>American farmers don’t need all those antibiotics.</p></a></li><li class="highlighted border-b" data-view="related-articles"><a href="/2015/04/04/opinion/big-businesss-critical-role-on-anti-gay-laws.html" data-link><div class="kicker">Editorial</div><img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2015/04/04/opinion/04sat1web/04sat1web-thumbLarge.jpg" class="highlighted-thumb" width="150" height="150"/><span class="title">Big Business and <span class="nobr">Anti-Gay</span> Laws</span><p>Corporations were right to speak out on this issue. They should take the same stand with their campaign spending.</p></a></li><li class="highlighted border-b" data-view="related-articles"><a href="/2015/04/03/opinion/a-promising-nuclear-deal-with-iran.html" data-link><div class="kicker">Editorial</div><img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/2015/04/03/opinion/03fri01editiorial/03fri01WEB-1428012213281-thumbLarge.jpg" class="highlighted-thumb" width="150" height="150"/><span class="title">A Promising Nuclear Deal With Iran</span><p>The preliminary agreement is a significant achievement that makes it more likely Iran will never be a nuclear threat.</p></a></li></ol></div></div></div><div class="footer" data-view="footer"><footer id="main-footer" class="main-footer" role="contentinfo"><div class="ad bottom " data-view="advert" data-position="bottom" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="hr-grayL2"></div><div class="footer-content"><div class="nav-tools"><div class="nav-tools-btn"><a href="#top" data-button="footer-back-to-top"><i class="icon icon-back-to-top"></i>Back to top</a></div></div></div><a name="sections"></a><nav id="sections-nav-tier1" class=